From a7145b75c50c8a875c1b6253efd71f90ac0239b4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: frqme <navecohen720@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 10:58:43 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] staging: greybus: uart: clear unsupported termios bits

The set_termios callback should clear any termios bits that the

hardware cannot support, so userspace is not misled into thinking

a setting took effect when it did not. Use tty_termios_copy_hw()

to restore hardware-related bits from the previous termios when

they cannot be applied.

Fixes a long-standing FIXME comment in gb_tty_set_termios().

Signed-off-by: frqme <navecohen720@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/staging/greybus/uart.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/greybus/uart.c b/drivers/staging/greybus/uart.c
index 7d060b4cd..a1cdf6d99 100644
--- a/drivers/staging/greybus/uart.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/greybus/uart.c
@@ -495,7 +495,9 @@ static void gb_tty_set_termios(struct tty_struct *tty,
 
 	newline.data_bits = tty_get_char_size(termios->c_cflag);
 
-	/* FIXME: needs to clear unsupported bits in the termios */
+	/* Don't claim to support bits we can't actually set */
+	if (termios_old)
+		tty_termios_copy_hw(termios, termios_old);
 	gb_tty->clocal = ((termios->c_cflag & CLOCAL) != 0);
 
 	if (C_BAUD(tty) == B0) {
-- 
2.53.0

